nf-claw — NOTICE

nf-claw was created by Danilo Monge (Eberhard Karls Universität Tübingen) and is
released under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

It adapts some files and its overall repository structure from ClawBio
(https://clawbio.ai), created by Manuel Corpas and released under the MIT
License. As required by MIT, ClawBio's copyright notice is retained in LICENSE.

The bioinformatics pipelines that nf-claw wraps come from the nf-core community
(https://nf-co.re) as git submodules under pipelines/<name>/upstream/. Each
upstream pipeline retains its own license and citation; see its
pipelines/<name>/upstream/ (e.g. its LICENSE and CITATIONS.md).

Provenance summary:
- runner/ and librarian/ — pipeline runtime and maintenance tooling for nf-claw.
- LICENSE, CITATION.cff, and the agent/human docs (CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md,
  README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md) started from ClawBio and were adapted/rewritten
  for nf-claw.
- pipelines/<name>/upstream/ — unmodified nf-core pipelines (pinned submodules).
- catalog.*, pipelines/<name>/skill.md and reference.md — generated from each
  pipeline's own nextflow_schema.json.

ClawBio reference:
  Corpas M. ClawBio: Bioinformatics-Native AI Agent Skill Library. Zenodo (2026).
  https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19420648
